    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "Office Memorandum • UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "TO : [REDACTED] DATE: October 13, 1958",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "FROM : [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING SAUCERS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "This memorandum summarizes Bureau policy regarding",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "unidentified flying objects commonly referred to as \"flying",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "saucers.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "Reports of \"flying saucers\" became prevalent in 1947 and at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "request of Army Air Forces Intelligence, Bureau agreed to cooperate in",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "investigation of flying discs. By Bureau Bulletin Number 42, 7-30-47,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "field instructed to investigate each instance to determine if bona fide",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "sighting, a prank, or hallucination. Coordination with Army through",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "liaison channels in field and at SOG.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "By letter 9-3-47 from Headquarters Air Defense Command addressed",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "to Commanding Generals of the various Air Forces it was noted original",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "intent of Air Force was that Air Force would interview responsible ob-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "servers and Bureau would investigate incidents of so-called discs found",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "on ground. Letter stated services of the FBI were enlisted in order to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "relieve the burdened Air Forces of the task of tracking down all the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "many instances which turned out to be \"trash can covers, toilet seats",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "and what not.\" As result, Bureau Bulletin Number 57 of 10/1/47 instructed",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "\"all future reports connected with flying discs should be referred to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "the Air Forces and no investigative action should be taken by Bureau",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "Agents.\" Letter of 9-27-47 advised Air Force that personnel and time",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "of FBI could not be dissipated in this manner (62-83894-121).",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "SAC Letter Number 30, 3-25-49, advised that from reliable",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "source it had been determined the USSR had been experimenting for four",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "years on unknown type of flying disc. SAC Letter listed for field data",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "desired by Air Force in connection with reports of sighting of flying",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "saucers. Letter again called attention to fact no investigation should",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "be conducted by Bureau but if reports made, information should be taken",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "and furnished to Air Force.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "SAC Letter Number 63, 6-29-52, referred to prior Bulletins",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "and SAC Letters and cautioned that the type of information desired by",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "Air Force should be obtained from complainants and furnished promptly",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "to CGI locally. This SAC Letter again reminded field investigation is",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "responsibility of Air Force.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "ESS:jas",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
